# 🔥 Firebase Setup Guide — Dream Solar Energies

Follow these steps to connect all 3 pages to your Firebase project in under 15 minutes.

---

## Step 1 — Create a Firebase Project

1. Go to **https://console.firebase.google.com**
2. Click **"Add project"** → name it `dream-solar-energies`
3. Disable Google Analytics (optional) → Click **"Create project"**

---

## Step 2 — Enable Authentication

1. In your Firebase project, go to **Build → Authentication**
2. Click **"Get started"**
3. Enable these sign-in providers:
   - ✅ **Email/Password** → Enable → Save
   - ✅ **Google** → Enable → add your support email → Save

---

## Step 3 — Create Firestore Database

1. Go to **Build → Firestore Database**
2. Click **"Create database"**
3. Choose **"Start in test mode"** (you'll add rules later)
4. Select your region (choose `asia-south1` for India) → Enable

### Firestore Collections (auto-created when first data is submitted):
| Collection | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `users` | Registered user profiles |
| `queries` | Customer solar queries from website |
| `installations` | Installation records added via admin |
| `testimonials` | Customer testimonials added via admin |
| `contactRequests` | Contact form submissions |

### Firestore Security Rules (paste in Firebase Console → Firestore → Rules):
```
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    // Users can read/write their own profile
    match /users/{userId} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
      allow read: if request.auth != null && get(/databases/$(database)/documents/users/$(request.auth.uid)).data.role == 'admin';
    }
    // Anyone (logged in or not) can submit queries
    match /queries/{queryId} {
      allow create: if true;
      allow read, update, delete: if request.auth != null && get(/databases/$(database)/documents/users/$(request.auth.uid)).data.role == 'admin';
    }
    // Same for contact requests
    match /contactRequests/{id} {
      allow create: if true;
      allow read, delete: if request.auth != null && get(/databases/$(database)/documents/users/$(request.auth.uid)).data.role == 'admin';
    }
    // Admin only for installations and testimonials
    match /installations/{id} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth != null && get(/databases/$(database)/documents/users/$(request.auth.uid)).data.role == 'admin';
    }
    match /testimonials/{id} {
      allow read: if true;
      allow write: if request.auth != null && get(/databases/$(database)/documents/users/$(request.auth.uid)).data.role == 'admin';
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Step 4 — Get Your Firebase Config

1. In Firebase Console → **Project Settings** (⚙️ gear icon)
2. Scroll to **"Your apps"** → Click **"Web"** (</> icon)
3. Register app name: `dream-solar-web` → Click **"Register app"**
4. Copy the `firebaseConfig` object — it looks like:

```javascript
const firebaseConfig = {
  apiKey: "AIzaSy...",
  authDomain: "dream-solar-energies.firebaseapp.com",
  projectId: "dream-solar-energies",
  storageBucket: "dream-solar-energies.appspot.com",
  messagingSenderId: "123456789",
  appId: "1:123456789:web:abc123..."
};
```

---

## Step 5 — Paste Config into All 3 Files

Open each file and **replace the placeholder config** with your real values:

### Files to update:
- `dream-solar-energies.html` — search for `YOUR_API_KEY`
- `login.html` — search for `YOUR_API_KEY`  
- `admin.html` — search for `YOUR_API_KEY`

In each file, replace:
```javascript
const firebaseConfig = {
  apiKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
  authDomain: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID.firebaseapp.com",
  projectId: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
  storageBucket: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID.appspot.com",
  messagingSenderId: "YOUR_SENDER_ID",
  appId: "YOUR_APP_ID"
};
```
With your actual config from Step 4.

---

## Step 6 — Set Up Your Admin Account

1. Open `login.html` in browser → Create account with your email
2. Go to **Firebase Console → Firestore → users collection**
3. Find your user document → Click it → Edit
4. Add field: `role` = `admin` (string)
5. Now you have full admin access to `admin.html`

---

## Step 7 — Deploy (Free Hosting with Firebase)

```bash
# Install Firebase CLI
npm install -g firebase-tools

# Login
firebase login

# Initialize in your project folder
firebase init hosting

# Deploy
firebase deploy
```

Your site will be live at: `https://dream-solar-energies.web.app`

---

## File Summary

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `dream-solar-energies.html` | Main public website |
| `login.html` | User login & registration |
| `admin.html` | Admin dashboard (manage queries, users, installs) |
| `FIREBASE_SETUP.md` | This guide |

